                        "designMd":  "---\nname: Enterprise Dark AI DevOps\ncolors:\n  surface: \u0027#0d1515\u0027\n  surface-dim: \u0027#0d1515\u0027\n  surface-bright: \u0027#333b3b\u0027\n  surface-container-lowest: \u0027#080f10\u0027\n  surface-container-low: \u0027#151d1e\u0027\n  surface-container: \u0027#192122\u0027\n  surface-container-high: \u0027#232b2c\u0027\n  surface-container-highest: \u0027#2e3637\u0027\n  on-surface: \u0027#dce4e5\u0027\n  on-surface-variant: \u0027#b9cacb\u0027\n  inverse-surface: \u0027#dce4e5\u0027\n  inverse-on-surface: \u0027#2a3233\u0027\n  outline: \u0027#849495\u0027\n  outline-variant: \u0027#3b494b\u0027\n  surface-tint: \u0027#00dbe9\u0027\n  primary: \u0027#dbfcff\u0027\n  on-primary: \u0027#00363a\u0027\n  primary-container: \u0027#00f0ff\u0027\n  on-primary-container: \u0027#006970\u0027\n  inverse-primary: \u0027#006970\u0027\n  secondary: \u0027#d1bcff\u0027\n  on-secondary: \u0027#3c0090\u0027\n  secondary-container: \u0027#7000ff\u0027\n  on-secondary-container: \u0027#ddcdff\u0027\n  tertiary: \u0027#fff5de\u0027\n  on-tertiary: \u0027#3b2f00\u0027\n  tertiary-container: \u0027#fed639\u0027\n  on-tertiary-container: \u0027#715d00\u0027\n  error: \u0027#ffb4ab\u0027\n  on-error: \u0027#690005\u0027\n  error-container: \u0027#93000a\u0027\n  on-error-container: \u0027#ffdad6\u0027\n  primary-fixed: \u0027#7df4ff\u0027\n  primary-fixed-dim: \u0027#00dbe9\u0027\n  on-primary-fixed: \u0027#002022\u0027\n  on-primary-fixed-variant: \u0027#004f54\u0027\n  secondary-fixed: \u0027#e9ddff\u0027\n  secondary-fixed-dim: \u0027#d1bcff\u0027\n  on-secondary-fixed: \u0027#23005b\u0027\n  on-secondary-fixed-variant: \u0027#5700c9\u0027\n  tertiary-fixed: \u0027#ffe179\u0027\n  tertiary-fixed-dim: \u0027#eac324\u0027\n  on-tertiary-fixed: \u0027#231b00\u0027\n  on-tertiary-fixed-variant: \u0027#554500\u0027\n  background: \u0027#0d1515\u0027\n  on-background: \u0027#dce4e5\u0027\n  surface-variant: \u0027#2e3637\u0027\ntypography:\n  h1:\n    fontFamily: Space Grotesk\n    fontSize: 32px\n    fontWeight: \u0027700\u0027\n    lineHeight: 40px\n    letterSpacing: -0.02em\n  h2:\n    fontFamily: Space Grotesk\n    fontSize: 24px\n    fontWeight: \u0027600\u0027\n    lineHeight: 32px\n    letterSpacing: -0.01em\n  body-lg:\n    fontFamily: Inter\n    fontSize: 18px\n    fontWeight: \u0027400\u0027\n    lineHeight: 28px\n  body-md:\n    fontFamily: Inter\n    fontSize: 16px\n    fontWeight: \u0027400\u0027\n    lineHeight: 24px\n  body-sm:\n    fontFamily: Inter\n    fontSize: 14px\n    fontWeight: \u0027400\u0027\n    lineHeight: 20px\n  code-sm:\n    fontFamily: Inter\n    fontSize: 13px\n    fontWeight: \u0027500\u0027\n    lineHeight: 18px\n    letterSpacing: 0.02em\n  label-caps:\n    fontFamily: Space Grotesk\n    fontSize: 12px\n    fontWeight: \u0027700\u0027\n    lineHeight: 16px\n    letterSpacing: 0.05em\nrounded:\n  sm: 0.25rem\n  DEFAULT: 0.5rem\n  md: 0.75rem\n  lg: 1rem\n  xl: 1.5rem\n  full: 9999px\nspacing:\n  unit: 4px\n  container-padding: 16px\n  stack-gap-sm: 8px\n  stack-gap-md: 16px\n  stack-gap-lg: 24px\n  grid-columns: \u00274\u0027\n  grid-gutter: 12px\n---\n\n## Brand \u0026 Style\n\nThe brand personality of this design system is **Intelligent, Authoritative, and Predictive**. It is engineered for DevOps engineers and SREs who require absolute clarity while managing complex cloud infrastructure via mobile. The emotional response should be one of \"calm control\"ˇŞthe user should feel that the AI is a silent, high-performance partner rather than an intrusive tool.\n\nThe design style utilizes a **Corporate Modern** foundation infused with **Glassmorphism** for data visualization layers. This creates a \"glass cockpit\" aestheticˇŞsophisticated dark surfaces with luminous accents that mimic high-end hardware interfaces. Visual weight is prioritized for critical system health indicators, ensuring that the most vital information is never obscured by decorative elements.\n\n## Colors\n\nThe palette is built on a **Deep Charcoal** foundation to minimize eye strain during long-tail incident management. The primary action color is **Electric Cyan**, a high-vibrancy hue that draws the eye immediately to primary CTAs and active deployment states.\n\nSecondary accents use a deep violet to represent AI-driven insights, creating a clear distinction between human-triggered actions and machine-generated suggestions. Semantic colors are refined for high accessibility against dark backgrounds:\n- **Success:** A vibrant emerald for healthy nodes and successful builds.\n- **Warning:** A warm amber for pending states or non-critical threshold breaches.\n- **Error:** A bright, high-contrast crimson for immediate intervention requirements.\n\n## Typography\n\nThe typographic hierarchy balances technical precision with high-density readability. This design system uses **Space Grotesk** for headlines and technical labels to lean into a futuristic, \"cutting-edge\" aesthetic. Its geometric nature provides a distinct look for metrics and status headers.\n\n**Inter** is utilized for all body copy, logs, and interactive UI elements. As a highly systematic font, it ensures that long streams of deployment logs or AI explanations remain legible at small sizes on mobile screens. For log data and terminal outputs, use the `code-sm` style with a medium weight to ensure every character is distinct.\n\n## Layout \u0026 Spacing\n\nThis design system employs a **Fluid Grid** model optimized for mobile devices. The core layout relies on a 4-column grid with 16px horizontal margins. A base unit of 4px is used to define all spacing, ensuring a consistent vertical rhythm.\n\nLayouts are primarily card-based to group related technical data (e.g., a \"Deployment\" card containing status, environment, and commit hash). Data density should be high but managed through \"progressive disclosure\"ˇŞusing stack gaps to separate logical sections while maintaining a compact footprint for monitoring multiple services simultaneously.\n\n## Elevation \u0026 Depth\n\nVisual hierarchy is established through **Tonal Layering** and **Glassmorphism**. Rather than using traditional shadows which can get lost in a dark UI, this design system uses surface color increments to denote \"height\":\n- **Level 0 (Background):** Deepest charcoal (`gray-900`), used for the main application canvas.\n- **Level 1 (Cards/Containers):** Slightly lighter (`gray-800`), used for the primary content containers.\n- **Level 2 (Overlays/Modals):** Lighter still (`gray-700`), with a 1px \"glass\" border (semi-transparent white at 10% opacity) to create a crisp edge.\n\nAI-driven insights or active voice input areas should use a **Backdrop Blur** (20px) and a subtle inner glow of the primary color to suggest they are \"floating\" or \"active\" above the standard system logs.\n\n## Shapes\n\nThe shape language is **Rounded**, reflecting a balance between professional software and approachable AI. \n- **Standard Cards/Inputs:** 0.5rem (8px) corner radius to provide a modern, clean structure.\n- **Action Buttons:** 1rem (16px) or fully pill-shaped to differentiate interactive elements from static informational cards.\n- **Status Pills:** Fully rounded (pill-shaped) to clearly distinguish them as semantic labels.\n\nCorners should be consistent across all elements within a group to maintain the systematic feel of the platform.\n\n## Components\n\n### Buttons \u0026 Inputs\n- **Primary Action:** Solid Electric Cyan background with black text for maximum contrast. High-gloss finish.\n- **Voice/AI Input:** A prominent, full-width text area at the bottom of the screen with a \"pulsing\" border when active. Includes a dedicated microphone icon with a cyan glow.\n- **Input Fields:** Dark gray background with a 1px border that shifts to cyan on focus.\n\n### Status Indicators \u0026 Progress\n- **Status Stream:** A vertical timeline component using micro-interactions. New logs \"slide and fade\" into view. \n- **Progress Indicators:** Linear, thin progress bars for deployments. Use a subtle glow effect on the leading edge of the progress bar to simulate \"energy\" or \"movement.\"\n\n### Cards\n- **Deployment Card:** Contains a header (Service Name), a sub-header (Environment), a status chip (Top-right), and a condensed log snippet (Bottom).\n- **Metric Card:** Focused on a single \"hero\" number with a sparkline background in the semantic color representing health.\n\n### Feedback Elements\n- **Micro-interactions:** When an AI action is processing, use a subtle \"shimmer\" effect across the primary card or input area rather than a traditional spinner, keeping the UI feeling high-tech and fluid.",
